## The three-layer contract (Karpathy pattern)

The vault has exactly three layers. Do not invent new ones.

| Layer | Role | LLM write access |
|---|---|---|
| `raw/` | Immutable source documents — provenance-stamped, one file per input | **READ ONLY.** Never edit, rename, or delete files under `raw/`. |
| `wiki/` | LLM-maintained structured knowledge — one canonical page per concept/entity/source/synthesis | Read and write. This is where you do your work. |
| `CLAUDE.md` | Schema — this file. Source of truth for routing, frontmatter, ops. | Read every session. Do not edit without explicit user request. |

The direction of flow is always `raw/` → `wiki/`. Never the reverse. `wiki/` is what you curate; `raw/` is what actually happened.

