## Folder map of `wiki/`

```
wiki/
├── index.md              ← master catalog — rebuilt on every ingest
├── log.md                ← append-only changelog of ops events
├── entities/             ← one canonical page per real-world thing
│   ├── people/
│   ├── companies/
│   ├── tools/
│   ├── books/
│   └── places/
├── concepts/             ← ideas and organizational scaffolding
│   ├── projects/         ← deadlined, actionable
│   ├── areas/            ← ongoing responsibilities
│   ├── resources/        ← reference material
│   ├── atoms/            ← single-idea notes (<300 words, densely linked)
│   ├── frameworks/       ← reusable mental models
│   └── archive/          ← deprecated, retained for history
├── sources/              ← one summary per ingested document
├── syntheses/            ← distilled output spanning multiple sources
│   ├── decisions/
│   ├── meetings/
│   ├── reflections/
│   └── reading-notes/
├── outputs/              ← query answers, lint reports, triage queue
└── external/             ← (optional) pages explicitly approved for external agents
```

Adapt leaf folders to the domain ({{DOMAIN_DESCRIPTION}}), but keep the top-level spine: `index.md`, `log.md`, `entities/`, `concepts/`, `sources/`, `syntheses/`, `outputs/`.

---

## Filename conventions

- All filenames: **kebab-case** — `david-chen.md`, not `David Chen.md`
- Source summaries from inbox: `{YYYYMMDD}-{slug}.md`
- Source summaries from articles: `{author}-{year}-{short-title}.md`
- Decisions: `{YYYY-MM-DD}-{slug}.md`
- Meetings: `{YYYY-MM-DD}-{participants-slug}.md`
- Weekly reflections: `{YYYY}-W{WW}-week.md`

---

## Wikilink rules

- Cross-references use Obsidian `[[wikilinks]]`, not markdown `[text](path)` links
- Link by path from the vault root, e.g. `[[entities/people/david-chen]]`
- Bold first occurrence of any key term per page
- Every new entity or concept page MUST be linked from at least one existing page (no orphans)
- When you rename a file, search for every `[[wikilink]]` pointing at it and update them in the same commit

